 Then,
 we define a Martin-Löf test by:
 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{n}$
\end_inset

 is generated by the strings of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{i_{1}}\dots\sigma_{i_{n}}$
\end_inset

.
 Then,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mu(S_{n})=\sum2^{-\abs{\sigma_{i_{1}}}-\dots-\abs{\sigma_{i_{n}}}}=\left(\sum2^{-\abs{\sigma}}\right)^{n}=(1-\mu(P))^{n}.
\]

\end_inset

