\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 and starting anew at the root,
 we will eventually 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 stop.
 Thus,
 we've reached a tail of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 that is in 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proposition
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop:mumlrclass"

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $P\subseteq\MLR$
\end_inset

