\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

.
 Thus,
 if the leftmost element of 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 really is Martin-Löf random,
 we will be describing some of its prefixes as efficiently as we can approximate 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(P)$
\end_inset

,
