\begin_inset Formula $U(\sigma)$
\end_inset

 is within 
\begin_inset Formula $2^{-n}$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(P)$
\end_inset

.
 Then,
 using 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

,
 we can find 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{N}$
\end_inset

 which is equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

,
 plus some set of measure at strictly less than 
\begin_inset Formula $2^{-n}$
\end_inset

.
 Thus,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(C_{N})<\mu(P)+2^{-n}$
\end_inset

,
 and so,
 if we look at the first depth 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 for which 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{N}$
\end_inset

 either adds or removes each string completely,
